How to Access Permissions Boundary

 AWS Console (Easiest)

# For IAM User:
1. Login → AWS Console
2. Search "IAM"
3. Left menu → "Users"
4. Click on username
5. Click "Permissions" tab
6. Scroll down → "Permissions Boundary"
7. Click "Set Boundary"
8. Select policy → Apply

# For IAM Role:
1. IAM → Roles
2. Click on role name
3. "Permissions" tab
4. "Permissions Boundary" → Set

Simple Rule

Create    →  IAM → Policies → Create Policy
Attach    →  IAM → Users/Roles → Permissions Boundary
Remove    →  IAM → Users/Roles → Remove Boundary
Verify    →  aws iam get-user / get-role
